<P>"Nod, the ability to almost ignore possible damage taken by using a shield and Shield Block is a big deal. You see, it puts slightly more difficult mobs in the Knight coulumn where survivability is not an issue when it is not pratical for Warriors to follow suit and S&amp;B as well, letting Knights focus more on their secondary abilities with these mobs which would have otherwise posed more of a challange for them."</P>
<P>You do realize that in lesser content you CAN go 2handed and ramp up your DPS.&nbsp; DPS IS your secondary role, and if you don't notice a major jump in DPS on lesser content you must be&nbsp;doing something seriously wrong.&nbsp; I don't see how S &amp; B would benefit you in lesser content...why do you need the extra avoidance and AC&nbsp;from&nbsp;shield in content were survivability isn't an issue? &nbsp;Also I don't want to hear you can't hold aggro either, I watch a warrior with a <A href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=71617" target=_blank>Polished Sunswordfrom </A>&nbsp;from DoN hold aggro off DW warriors in raids for crying out loud.&nbsp; This is versus a warrior using Champion's Sword of Eternal Power &amp; Dragon Scale-Bladed Mace&nbsp; In addition to the innate aggro mulitplier on the sword he has CS IV and Enraging blow augs.&nbsp; On the mace he has another enraging blow aug.&nbsp; Yet with the polished sunword the other warrior can steal and HOLD aggro off him, seems like adequate aggro in 2H setup to me.&nbsp; Heck BB in less than cutting edge content knights don't even bother with a shield if they have a good 2hander, since the 2 hander is still more DPS than the high ratio one handers.</P>
