			>
			<div></div><p>I will use shields sometimes whenI solo, but yes generally in wussy content I'll go with a twohander for the dps.</p><p>BB they do raise valid points about ac, if your ac is considerably inferior to say a knight with 10k not only will you get hit more but you will get hit much harder. Haveing lots of hps doesn't mean anything if mobs hit for max near every hit. The key islooseing those hps you do have asslowly as possible.</p><p>BB much as you like to use your old class discription, it isn't realavent in todays game. Yes warriors have certain issues that need to be addressed. However, they won't be addressed in realation to your old discription. They will be evaluated based on the three tanks viability in all group settings while each maintaining a primary roll in raids.</p><p>Your not the &quot;one and only&quot; tank, your 1 of 3. Kinda like the Borg in a way. Each tank has certain attributes that make them useful for certain situations. Also, each tank is equipt well enough to be a viable option in any group encounter at any progression level. No more is there a &quot;need&quot; for a warrior or you can't do the content. A knight of the same progression level can do the job too.</p><p>SoE pretty much reguardsknights as groupable primary tanks with specific raid rolesand warriors as groupable primary tanks with specific raid roles. I do agree your secondary ability is melee dps, while my secondary ability is overall dps via spells/pet and melee.</p><p>Sk's pulling was never by intent it simply came about by happenstance. I certainly don't recomend haveing sk's pull in content with alot of casters. I don't personally pull much unless I'm also tanking, andI have pulled for my raiding guild maybe three times in the entire year. I'm a tank that can pull if we can't find a real puller.</p><p>I know you disagree with much of how I think BB, that's fine. I'm not at war with the warriors in my guild, thier perfectly fine with me being the perverbial &quot;loose cannon&quot;. Despite the bad conotations of such a statement, the guild actually does give me free reign to roam around the battle field and agro what everI think needs it. I don't get direct assignments about what to off tank or what have yain half our raids, they just let me do what ever it isI do. They trust me to find the trouble spot and charge into it like a crazy person.</p>	
