		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<div></div><div>I've been a strong proponent of warriors receiving a downward scaling tool for some time...mock is a smallish version of a downward scaling tool which can help some, but I feel more is needed.</div><div></div><div>Now, interestingly, our best downward scaling tool is our discipline &quot;Aura of Runes&quot;... which is actually now been given to SK's in PoRo, but in a much better form (mana based vs. end based, much shorter refresh, etc etc).</div><div></div><div>The primary issue is one of content though, as long as content is kept to a certain point where a specific level of durability is called for, then it's less necessary. I'm going to hold out on PoRo to see how it all falls, and what becomes the popular hunting grounds etc.</div><div></div><div>It's no secret that during Dragons, this was a huge issue, since content had been getting progressively weaker, but that was somewhat alleviated in Depths. As I said, we'll have to see what Ro has in store before making any definitive judgements, but in terms of mob DPS output, stunnability, number of HP, and so on, there will be a way to determine how important this is... it's probably a good idea to get thinking about this downward scaling tool anyhow, so that it doesn't become a crisis when it IS needed, but that tool isn't going to be shield block, that's upward scaling, not downward scaling.</div><div></div><div></div>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
