		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			"The primary issue is one of content though, as long as content is kept
to a certain point where a specific level of durability is called for,
then it's less necessary. "<br><br>The problem though Frodlin is that Knights being able to routinely use shields and Shield Block and these capabilities being unpractical for Warriors reduces the amount of content where Warrrior greater survivability is an asset. It frees Knights from having to devote as much mana to simply staying healthy and allows them insted to focus more on secondary group friendly capabilites.<br><br>There are actually three problems and content is merely one of them:<br><br>1. Content.<br><br>2. Knights narrowing the survivability gap and therefore reducing the amount of content where grouping a Warrior is an advantage.<br><br>3. The lack of Warrior utility having the same weight as pulling, ressing, buffing, healing.<br><br>We are intended to tank better. We are intended to do heavy DPS. We are intended to be able to obtain and hold aggro.<br><br>Warriors not having practical use from shields and Shield Block given the amount of survivability narrowing these two things confer on Knights IS one of the major issues now facing us. With this advantage, a Knight can tank more content just as effectively as I can AND provide additional group friendly utility. With me having practical use from it and doing the heavy melee DPS Warriorrs are entitled to do, there is a choice -<br><br>get a Wariror with more survivability and heavy DPS<br>or a Knight with marginal survivabity and enormous versatility.<br><br>Without it, the choice is get a Warrior no less likely to die and heavy DPS when he's not cutting it in half by using Defensive<br>or a Knight just as likely to survive and with enormous versatility.<br><br>A little more DPS != the weight of Knight utility anywhere.<br><div></div>	
		</td></tr>
