<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<HR>
Battleblade-Xegony wrote:</P>
<P>The problem though Frodlin is that Knights being able to routinely use shields and Shield Block and these capabilities being unpractical for Warriors reduces the amount of content where Warrrior greater survivability is an asset. It frees Knights from having to devote as much mana to simply staying healthy and allows them insted to focus more on secondary group friendly capabilites.<BR>
<HR>
</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>And that's a problem how, exactly?&nbsp; Our 'group friendly capabilities' can all be performed much, MUCH better by another class that provides MUCH better DPS,&nbsp;and most of the time&nbsp;much more utility.</P>
<P>Their are few specific quests in which our 'group friendly capabilities' may be advantageous, like a ShadowKnight pulling 70.2 w/ Nullify Magic and Snaring...&nbsp; or a Paladin offering undead DPS and group heals in Longshadow.1 or 3... and there are missions that have HUGE advantages given to Warriors like 68.3's and&nbsp;70.1's Guardians...</P>
<P>Also, aside from the challenging content you've seen in DoD in both regular and hard missions, you've recieved a group dodge increaser shout, and you're now getting a group procrate aura and AC boost... meaning they're adding some 'group friendly capability' to the Warrior class for the last 2 expansions, while you've yet to change your sad, tired, argument.</P>
