			>
			<div></div><br><blockquote><hr>Battleblade-Xegony wrote:<br>&quot;The primary issue is one of content though, as long as content is kept to a certain point where a specific level of durability is called for, then it's less necessary. &quot;<br><br>The problem though Frodlin is that Knights being able to routinely use shields and Shield Block and these capabilities being unpractical for Warriors reduces the amount of content where Warrrior greater survivability is an asset.<strong> It frees Knights from having to devote as much mana to simply staying healthy and allows them insted to focus more on secondary group friendly capabilites.<br></strong><br><hr></blockquote><p><br>Your assertation here is incorrect Battleblade.</p><p>Using a shield reduces our melee aggro by a significantly largeamount. That in turnrequires us to utilize more mana for maintaining our aggro and thusreduces our secondary abilities (which require that mana).</p><p>When we reach the threshhold where shields become redundant, there is no need (with or without the shield) for us to utilize our mana on keeping healthy anyways. This is the job of the group healer and any unneeded heals being cast by theknight when the group healer is good on mana is simply a waste of our own mana.</p><p>its at this point where knights shoudl switch over to a 2-hander for better DPS, as not only is this more useful, but also it gives us better melee aggro reducing our need to spend mana on aggro and thus giving us more manato <em>&quot;instead to focus more on secondary group friendly capabilites.&quot;</em></p><p><strong>&quot;We are intended to tank better. We are intended to do heavy DPS. We are intended to be able to obtain and hold aggro&quot;</strong></p><p>What does this have to do with shields and downward scaling tools? If you want better downward scaling tools and heavy DPS, and better aggro, shouldn't you be more focused on maxxing your DPS or aggro. Switching over to your maximum set-ups when dealing with easier content?</p><p>I mean really, when you don't need to be a powerhouse Tank, why would you ever switch to a shield and take Any hit to your DPS and Aggro? Not even for a 1% hit would you switch out to a shield. For downward scaling you should be wanting to grab a 2-hander and go to town. Or Duel Wielding and aggroing mobs as fast as you can blink as you plow through them.</p><p>You would not be wanting a damned shield!</p><p></p><p></p>	
