			>
			<div></div>For once I agree 100% with Frodlin.<br><br>Currently all tank classes have some sort of defensive proc for reducing (or healing) damage.&nbsp; The warrior ability, aura of runes, which was the first to be introduced, is the weakest.&nbsp; I don't see why this shouldn't be ramped up to be similar in capability to what pallies and SK's get from their PoR abilities (or shocking defense, as I suggested earlier- I forgot about aura of runes, that probably makes more sense as it's already closer to what it would need to be).<br><br>I've been saying for..... probably a year that content needs to be ramped up to keep up with the vast increase in player power in Omens, which accelerated in DoD and PoR, through the addition of single-group gear far beyond what was previously available.&nbsp; DoD raised the difficulty bar quite a bit over DoN, but people that don't raid at all should be able to obtain gear to be able to handle content that's quite a bit harder than what's generally available in single-group missions (I'll caveat that by saying I've done very little in PoR so far with regards to missions, so I don't know for sure what that's done).&nbsp; <br><br>I'd love to see the addition of 1-group missions that scale on up to the high end raider- if there's 1-group missions that a demiplane equipped tank gets a real challenge out of, but is extremely difficult, if not impossible at my present progression stage- great.&nbsp; It gives me something to look forward to.&nbsp; At present, I don't know of many missions that present more than moderate challenges to my capabilities as a tank.&nbsp; That's not a class balance issue- that's an issue with content.<br><div></div><br>Battleblade,<br><br>Shields STILL don't grant any downward scaling benifits, any more than they did on page one of this thread.&nbsp; Whether or not that's an issue, shields are still irrelevant to this topic.<br><p>Message Edited by josahd on <span class=date_text>02-28-2006</span> <span class