			Giggle, multi-tanking.<br><br>My niche is hard hitting content that Knights can not manage - that is the <u>only</u> reason I rolled a Wariror. Nibble away at that niche by giving Knights Knight Defensive, make shields and Shield Block impractical for Warriors, and fiddle with group content until there is not a meaningful quantity of mobs requiring my Central Class Defining Capabilities that should not have been shared and you end up with Warriors suggesting things like:<br><br>multi-tanking<br>or in my case Intimidating Stare<br><br>It's pretty bad when our class definintion means taking a little less damage, aggroing less at first but had the mob lived for two minutes, which they don't do in group content, having built up rock solid aggro, and doing "heavy" damage - unless you compare us to Paladins with now 20K+ HP swings or we are using sword and board to preserve our intended survival advantages rather than conceed them to powerful half casters.<br><br>I don't need downward scaling capability. I need hard as nails group content with nice crisp high DI. Content that gives Warirors their intended advantage and removes parity in our intended strength with hybrids while they retain bucketloads of utility.<br><br>Multi-tank??!! I'd sooner dye my armor lavander and ride a Unicorn bareback.<br><div></div>	
