nt which y'all have NEVER asked for and Knight's asking for EoA on equipment rather than Warriors having foolishly suggesting it (as I and Frodlin both did).<br><br>If you are going to make stuff up then kindly restrict it to pretending your best heal is 1200HPs like other have. Some uninformed players night buy that load, but they are not about to buy the fish you are selling.<br><br>At least Josahd was honest (greedy/godmode preserving, but forthright about it) - he wants shield use to remain an advantagous gap closer for Knights and does not want Warriors also enjoying 100AC+ of AC not subject to the softcap.<br><br>The unfair advantage Knights have makes more content fall in the catagory where Knight versatility exceeds the value of greater Warrior survivability. The answer is making shields and shield block practical for Warriors and increasing content difficulty or at least the spread and the difficulty of the harder 10% of the content.<br><br>Do that and Warriors don't end up suggesting that maybe we ought to be able to multi-tank the relative moss-snakes appearing in most current content. No thanks, I prefer my mobs to hit bone-jarringly hard and not see Clerics, Shaman, Beastlords, Monks and half-caster/half-warriors (Paladins, SK's and Rangers) tanking them with ease.<br><div></div><p>Message Edited by Battleblade-Xegony on <span class=date_text>03-01-2006</span> <span class=time_text>02:58 AM</span>	
