			>
			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
togam wrote:<BR>
<DIV>i&nbsp; have a&nbsp; simple&nbsp; solution&nbsp; ,&nbsp; but&nbsp; noone&nbsp; will like it .</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>make all&nbsp; critters&nbsp; do a&nbsp; 3&nbsp;second silence to the&nbsp;character &nbsp;under aggro . make it&nbsp; such&nbsp;that&nbsp; you can't&nbsp; discipline or&nbsp; cast&nbsp; while under aggro , you&nbsp; would have to&nbsp; do&nbsp; it&nbsp; after&nbsp; aggro&nbsp; has changed to&nbsp; someone else (or your corpse)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>this solution&nbsp; removes&nbsp; the spellbook&nbsp;from&nbsp; everyone while under aggro , it&nbsp; removes&nbsp; disciplines&nbsp; and procs . it&nbsp; basically&nbsp; removes&nbsp; all&nbsp; character advantages&nbsp; that&nbsp; allow people who&nbsp; solo&nbsp; to&nbsp; solo&nbsp; thus&nbsp; making them&nbsp; play&nbsp; in&nbsp; groups . the only&nbsp; downside&nbsp; to&nbsp; this&nbsp; would be FD and&nbsp; jolt/concussion&nbsp; line spells ,those&nbsp; spell lines are used&nbsp; specifically&nbsp; to&nbsp; drop&nbsp;personal&nbsp; aggro . maybe put&nbsp; a&nbsp; range on&nbsp;the silence of say&nbsp; 50 '&nbsp; (thats&nbsp; half&nbsp; the range of bellow or&nbsp; base complete heal)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>downward scaling&nbsp; would immediatly&nbsp; be repaired because&nbsp; basically&nbsp; everything&nbsp; would then&nbsp; require a group of some sort&nbsp;.</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>And also a secondary effect of 6 seconds where procs won't go off and all foci melee/aggro aren't accounted for the base 3 seconds.&nbsp;&nbsp;And make it unresistable and trigger every time the mob swings!!!	
